LuÃ­s Filipe Bernardes

2
00:00:48,646 --> 00:00:53,650
I don't want any of you newspapermen
trying a hidden camera stunt on me.

3
00:00:53,651 --> 00:00:56,278
This isn't a public exhibition.

4
00:00:56,279 --> 00:00:59,198
And you folks who have never seen
anything of this kind before,

5
00:00:59,199 --> 00:01:02,078
remember, no talking.

6
00:01:02,209 --> 00:01:06,288
No matter what anybody says or does,
you keep quiet.

7
00:01:06,389 --> 00:01:09,008
Even if John Allen himself should
talk to you,

8
00:01:09,160 --> 00:01:10,900
don't dare answer him.

9
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,755
It doesn't seem quite fair no to talk.

10
00:01:12,756 --> 00:01:16,175
We ought to try to make his last few
minutes as pleasant as possible.

11
00:01:16,176 --> 00:01:18,300
Oh, shut up!

12
00:01:18,301 --> 00:01:20,100
I'm not worried about him.

13
00:01:20,264 --> 00:01:23,267
He'll faint dead away
as soon as the show starts.

14
00:01:24,368 --> 00:01:26,803
- All set?
- Yes, sir.

15
00:01:26,904 --> 00:01:29,197
Well then, we'll start the parade.

16
00:01:37,933 --> 00:01:41,000
Why doesn't he want us to answer
John Allen if he talks to us?

17
00:01:41,195 --> 00:01:44,708
Why did you come up here anyway?
There ain't gonna be any legs in this show.

18
00:01:46,509 --> 00:01:50,679
Well, you see, I'm taking a lot
of sociology courses at college.

19
00:01:50,780 --> 00:01:53,384
So Prof. Summers, he teaches us, you know,

20
00:01:53,385 --> 00:01:55,780
thought it would be a good thing if
one of us could report to the group...

21
00:01:55,781 --> 00:01:57,780
...the actual process of an execution.

22
00:01:57,800 --> 00:02:00,809
So he selected me and got me
a pass from the governor.

23
00:02:00,810 --> 00:02:01,910
College boy, huh?

24
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:04,800
Well, you'll get your belly
full of it up here alright.

25
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:07,999
Doctor?

26
00:02:08,108 --> 00:02:11,311
You tell me, will you? Why can't
we answer John Allen back?

27
00:02:11,412 --> 00:02:14,306
It's because Allen is living
on his nerve now.

28
00:02:14,407 --> 00:02:17,351
If he talks at all it will be
to keep up his courage.

29
00:02:17,452 --> 00:02:19,212
He really doesn't expect an answer.

30
00:02:19,313 --> 00:02:21,290
If you gave him one, it would likely
throw him off.

31
00:02:21,291 --> 00:02:24,043
And we'd have a devil of a time
with him, hysteria and all that,

32
00:02:24,044 --> 00:02:25,564
fighting to keep out of the chair.

33
00:02:25,565 --> 00:02:27,945
I don't know about that. He seemed
pretty cool when I talked to him.

34
00:02:27,965 --> 00:02:29,800
- When was that?
- Yesterday.

35
00:02:29,801 --> 00:02:31,354
What did he have to say?

36
00:02:31,355 --> 00:02:34,455
Does he still persist that we're
burning him at the wrong time?

37
00:02:34,465 --> 00:02:37,000
- Yep.
- There's something in what he says, too.

38
00:02:37,001 --> 00:02:38,201
I don't know about that.

39
00:02:38,301 --> 00:02:43,800
Look, doctor, when that current's
turned on, how long will it take before...

40
00:02:43,828 --> 00:02:47,400
- ...it's all over?
- You mean before I'll pronounce him dead?

41
00:02:47,569 --> 00:02:50,000
No, before he actually is dead.

42
00:02:50,042 --> 00:02:53,000
Will he pass out as soon
as the current hits him?

43
00:02:53,001 --> 00:02:54,001
- No.
- He won't?

44
00:02:54,022 --> 00:02:55,800
I thought it was all over
just like that.

45
00:02:55,801 --> 00:02:58,201
Not with a powerful fellow
like John Allen.

46
00:02:58,398 --> 00:03:00,300
His body will be paralyzed,

47
00:03:00,341 --> 00:03:05,389
but his brain will continue to
function for... maybe two seconds.

48
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:08,158
Gee!

49
00:03:08,168 --> 00:03:11,900
Those will be the longest
two seconds he ever lived.

50
00:03:11,999 --> 00:03:15,700
Long enough for him to relive
his whole life.

51
00:03:16,551 --> 00:03:18,137
He's due now.

52
00:03:27,615 --> 00:03:32,487
...and whosoever liveth and
believeth in me shall never die.

53
00:03:34,338 --> 00:03:39,200
He that believeth in me,
though he were dead, yet shall he live.

54
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:42,838
I know that my redeemer liveth
and that he shall...

55
00:03:44,299 --> 00:03:46,761
...and stand at the latter day
upon the earth.

56
00:03:46,762 --> 00:03:50,850
And though after my skin
and bones destroyed...

57
00:04:22,726 --> 00:04:24,694
John!

58
00:04:24,861 --> 00:04:28,680
- John Allen!
- That's me. What is it, big boy?

59
00:04:28,757 --> 00:04:32,600
- My drill went dead. Is the plug in?
- Wait, I'll see.

60
00:04:37,242 --> 00:04:39,900
Yeah, it's in. What's wrong?

61
00:04:39,932 --> 00:04:42,999
- Got a screwdriver?
- Wait a minute.

62
00:04:53,485 --> 00:04:55,637
- Here you are.
- Thanks.

63
00:04:55,669 --> 00:04:57,450
- What time is it?
- Near five.

64
00:04:57,478 --> 00:05:01,150
I don't want to be late quitting.
I ain't giving this outfit no free overtime.

65
00:05:01,176 --> 00:05:03,200
Anyway, not when I have
a heavy date on.

66
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:07,100
Say, listen, Bud, I don't think I'm gonna
horn in on your party tonight.

67
00:05:07,135 --> 00:05:08,794
Getting stuck up all of a sudden,
are you?

68
00:05:08,795 --> 00:05:10,436
Me and Annie ain't good enough
for you anymore.

69
00:05:10,437 --> 00:05:13,337
Oh, it ain't that and you know it.
It's only that...

70
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:16,903
Well, I don't know who the dame is
Annie's gonna bring along for me.

71
00:05:16,904 --> 00:05:20,600
- I ain't so keen about a blind date.
- Ah, she'll be alright.

72
00:05:20,648 --> 00:05:24,120
Annie knows you're particular
about dames. She'll get you a good number.

73
00:05:24,121 --> 00:05:26,623
Yeah? Well what about that truck horse
she picked out for me last time?

74
00:05:26,624 --> 00:05:29,770
- I gave her the devil for it, didn't I?
- A lot of good it did me.

75
00:05:29,771 --> 00:05:31,999
I was stuck with her for
a whole evening.

76
00:05:32,015 --> 00:05:35,598
Boy, all that dame wanted to do
was eat. Eat and dance.

77
00:05:35,699 --> 00:05:38,010
I felt like I was handling
the rear end of a fire truck.

78
00:05:38,711 --> 00:05:41,264
I told Annie that.
She knows better now.

79
00:05:41,265 --> 00:05:44,100
Now you call her up and tell her it's
cold turkey with me for tonight.

80
00:05:44,166 --> 00:05:47,571
A can't do that now, John,
Annie's got a dame all set up.

81
00:05:48,472 --> 00:05:50,380
Well, what's this one to be like?

82
00:05:50,408 --> 00:05:53,043
I don't know, but she ain't
gonna be no fireman's delight.

83
00:05:53,194 --> 00:05:56,280
This baby's gonna be alright.
She's got class, Annie says.

84
00:05:56,389 --> 00:06:00,077
- Works in a laundry
- Well I hope she's got class.

85
00:06:00,078 --> 00:06:02,830
Hey, listen now, I ain't promised
you no Peggy Joyce.

86
00:06:02,831 --> 00:06:05,882
Oh, that's all right. I ain't
expecting anything much.

87
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:09,171
After all a laundry is where
you send your dirty clothes.

88
00:06:09,672 --> 00:06:11,948
Hey, you know, Bud...

89
00:06:12,999 --> 00:06:17,537
Working this way, 20, 25 stories
up in the air, you know...

90
00:06:17,739 --> 00:06:19,832
It kinda gives a fellow ideas.

91
00:06:20,499 --> 00:06:24,787
You know, you meet a guy
or a girl down there...

92
00:06:24,888 --> 00:06:26,648
...and they think they're hot stuff,
they amount to something.

93
00:06:26,649 --> 00:06:28,810
Well, there ain't nothing wrong
in them being that, is there?

94
00:06:28,911 --> 00:06:31,213
No, nothing wrong,
nothing like that, but...

95
00:06:31,414 --> 00:06:36,492
I don't know... when you get
up here and look down on them...

96
00:06:36,794 --> 00:06:39,871
Well, you get a different slant
on the whole thing.

97
00:06:40,772 --> 00:06:45,735
You know, they only seem like...
like just a crawling bunch of little flies.

98
00:06:45,836 --> 00:06:48,488
Look at them, look at them
crawling down there.

99
00:06:48,589 --> 00:06:52,000
A banker, and a lawyer,
and a fancy dame.

100
00:06:52,168 --> 00:06:54,821
All the rest of them thinking
they're doing big things.

101
00:06:54,922 --> 00:06:57,224
Making speeches, and getting
into the papers and...

102
00:06:57,225 --> 00:06:59,727
cheating and hating each other.

103
00:07:01,428 --> 00:07:04,180
I'll betcha God gets a big laugh
out of this old world.

104
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:06,868
Hey, listen, if you're gonna talk
carelesslike about God,

105
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:09,696
don't pick out no six-inch
girder to do it on.

106
00:07:10,397 --> 00:07:12,741
Don't it ever hit you that way too?

107
00:07:12,742 --> 00:07:16,336
Look, John, you and me's been bunking
together for more than two years now,

108
00:07:16,367 --> 00:07:19,256
...and I ain't never heard you pull off
anything like this before.

109
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:23,252
- You got me scared.
- It scares me too sometimes.

110
00:07:23,365 --> 00:07:26,593
You're in a bad way.
Better take some aspirins.

111
00:07:26,794 --> 00:07:30,245
First thing I know you'll be going sour on me.
You'll be clipping some of them coupons...

112
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:32,886
...and getting yourself a study
book to carry around.

113
00:07:32,906 --> 00:07:34,808
That mightn't be a bad idea at that.

114
00:07:34,809 --> 00:07:37,119
Oh, no, not while you're
bunking with me.

115
00:07:37,170 --> 00:07:40,700
- I ain't gonna live with no lily.
- Well, don't you worry.

116
00:07:40,857 --> 00:07:43,860
The girl I'm gonna fall for
is gonna have real class.

117
00:07:43,861 --> 00:07:46,188
I ain't seen no poodle dogs
chasing you.

118
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,217
Yeah, well she's gonna have
an education.

119
00:07:48,718 --> 00:07:51,200
A girl you can learn something from.

120
00:07:51,228 --> 00:07:53,195
Ain't no use in both of
us being dumb.

121
00:07:53,296 --> 00:07:57,083
Hey, what do you want to go bothering
your head about that education bunk for?

122
00:07:57,084 --> 00:08:00,871
Ain't you making 62.50 a week?
Well, what more do you want?

123
00:08:00,882 --> 00:08:04,977
A guy told me that $62.50 is more
than what a college professor makes.

124
00:08:04,999 --> 00:08:08,762
Do you want to be a college professor, not
have any dough to blow in on a good time?

125
00:08:08,764 --> 00:08:11,674
No, it ain't the money, Bud,
it ain't that. It's only...

126
00:08:11,683 --> 00:08:14,151
Gee, I don't know, there's...

127
00:08:14,952 --> 00:08:17,479
There's so much in the world
I don't know.

128
00:08:17,581 --> 00:08:20,200
One thing you sure don't know is
when you're well off.

129
00:08:20,343 --> 00:08:22,200
Yeah, I guess you're right, Bud.

130
00:08:22,353 --> 00:08:26,000
I don't know why I should be wanting
them kind of things.

131
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:29,800
You know, it's being up here
so close to the sky...

132
00:08:29,953 --> 00:08:31,552
...makes a guy think crazy.

133
00:08:31,573 --> 00:08:34,100
You leave the stinking racket
to the guys what gets paid for it.

134
00:08:34,133 --> 00:08:36,142
You know, like college professors.

135
00:08:36,243 --> 00:08:40,300
You and me, we ain't got no time to think.
We got work to do.

136
00:08:40,334 --> 00:08:43,218
- Oh, you said it.
- There's only one thing we gotta think about.

137
00:08:43,219 --> 00:08:47,608
When we get our arms around
a dame, how far can we go?

138
00:08:52,312 --> 00:08:53,380
Hello?

139
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,788
Oh, hello.

140
00:08:55,975 --> 00:08:58,900
Yeah, sure.
I did? How much?

141
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:02,353
Thirty-eight bucks? Oh boy!

142
00:09:02,590 --> 00:09:06,216
Yeah, sure!
Where's the payoff?

143
00:09:06,410 --> 00:09:09,400
Don't worry, I'll be there on time.

144
00:09:09,455 --> 00:09:11,818
John! John!

145
00:09:12,018 --> 00:09:14,200
John! John!

146
00:09:15,428 --> 00:09:18,900
Hey John, can you top it? I pulled
a winner, Peach Blossom in the third.

147
00:09:18,999 --> 00:09:21,176
- Yeah, how much did you make?
- Thirty-eight bucks.

148
00:09:21,277 --> 00:09:23,137
- Gee, not bad.
- Not bad?

149
00:09:23,138 --> 00:09:25,400
Thirty-eight bucks without
lifting a finger.

150
00:09:25,401 --> 00:09:28,001
Say, where would I be if I could
pull one like that every day?

151
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:30,780
You lost over thirty-eight
on the ponies last month alone.

152
00:09:30,888 --> 00:09:34,129
Aw, that don't count. The bookie's
paying off in front of Tony's place.

153
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:36,903
I'll phone the girls to meet us there,
we'll go out and throw the works.

154
00:09:37,799 --> 00:09:39,940
Say, you ain't gonna blow in
the whole 38!

155
00:09:39,965 --> 00:09:43,869
I sure am. You don't spend easy
money fast, no more will come to you.

156
00:09:43,870 --> 00:09:48,500
Oh, yeah, but it seems crazy to spend
all that jack on a couple of dumb dames.

157
00:09:48,556 --> 00:09:51,700
I ain't gonna spend it on the dames.
It's on us.

158
00:09:51,753 --> 00:09:54,500
A couple of ties for you
and a silk shirt for me.

159
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:58,500
I seen a beauty the other day,
I'm gonna get it. Blue silk it was.

160
00:09:58,501 --> 00:10:00,701
What's left of the thirty-eight
goes to the girls.

161
00:10:01,822 --> 00:10:04,333
Why did I only have two bucks
on that night?

162
00:10:04,434 --> 00:10:07,786
If I'd had 20 smacks on them
I'd have made... let me see...

163
00:10:07,887 --> 00:10:10,657
- I got 38 for two, that's er...
- 380.

164
00:10:10,658 --> 00:10:14,388
Three-eighty, that's right!
Can you imagine it, three-eighty.

165
00:10:14,436 --> 00:10:16,100
Yeah, you might just as soon
have lost your twenty.

166
00:10:16,101 --> 00:10:19,280
Not me, I've hit my stride,
I'm on a lucky streak now.

167
00:10:19,309 --> 00:10:22,537
Last time you hit a lucky streak
I had to pay all the room rent.

168
00:10:22,538 --> 00:10:25,533
Oh, what a guy. No wonder
the girls don't like you.

169
00:10:25,634 --> 00:10:28,200
Oh, they like me well enough.

170
00:10:28,302 --> 00:10:31,346
Say, didn't that fire wagon
slobber all over me?

171
00:10:32,447 --> 00:10:34,300
That's because you were
feeding her good.

172
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:38,201
If Annie's got you a thin one this time,
I'll bet she won't even give you a tumble.

173
00:10:38,219 --> 00:10:40,631
Yeah, well that will her tough luck.

174
00:10:40,832 --> 00:10:44,952
I ain't wasting any time on losing any sleep
over any dame that comes out of a laundry.

175
00:10:47,031 --> 00:10:48,857
You know? You know, John,

176
00:10:48,858 --> 00:10:50,958
you oughtn't to razz a dame
you ain't never seen before.

177
00:10:50,999 --> 00:10:54,200
After all, she's taking just
as big a chance as you are.

178
00:10:54,658 --> 00:10:57,226
Yeah? Say, now look here.

179
00:10:57,468 --> 00:11:01,230
Any time I take a dame out
she knows what it is to be out.

180
00:11:01,331 --> 00:11:04,177
- I satisfy.
- Oh, yeah?

181
00:11:04,268 --> 00:11:09,200
# Oh, boy, I'm lucky G-boy, #
# I'm lucky, this is my lucky day #

182
00:11:25,483 --> 00:11:30,854
Boy, 38 bucks and nothing to do but
spend them, and am I gonna spend them.

183
00:11:30,895 --> 00:11:32,863
I betcha that bookie won't
even show up.

184
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,786
Oh, he'll be here, he can't
afford to pull a trick like that.

185
00:11:35,787 --> 00:11:37,664
I've been laying bets
with this guy for months.

186
00:11:37,665 --> 00:11:39,280
Yeah, well, how many times
have you won?

187
00:11:39,375 --> 00:11:43,242
Take it from me, John, a guy don't
get rich slaving away for wages.

188
00:11:43,313 --> 00:11:45,047
It's the guys that...

189
00:11:53,498 --> 00:11:56,010
Gee, that's a hot job.

190
00:11:56,211 --> 00:11:57,881
I didn't notice.

191
00:11:57,911 --> 00:12:00,813
Aw, lay off of that fly stuff,
you're down on the level now.

192
00:12:00,915 --> 00:12:02,983
You know, I'm sorry I dated
Annie up tonight.

193
00:12:02,984 --> 00:12:05,000
With all the extra coin
coming in I coulda...

194
00:12:05,025 --> 00:12:08,698
No, Bud, that stuff is alright
when a guy is on the loose.

195
00:12:08,699 --> 00:12:11,293
- But what about you and Annie?
- I ain't married yet, am I?

196
00:12:11,314 --> 00:12:14,162
- You're engaged.
- Don't tie me down yet.

197
00:12:14,163 --> 00:12:17,483
Till the preacher makes me say love,
honor and obey,

198
00:12:17,584 --> 00:12:19,928
I can still have a little fun.

199
00:12:22,621 --> 00:12:26,024
Gee, she had a nifty leg.
I shouldn't have let her get away.

200
00:12:26,125 --> 00:12:29,000
Hey, Bud!
Hello there!

201
00:12:29,129 --> 00:12:31,632
Say, I pulled a fast one
on you this time, didn't I?

202
00:12:31,733 --> 00:12:34,550
- Sure did. How Much you got coming to you?
- Thirty-eight smacks is what you said.

203
00:12:34,579 --> 00:12:38,989
- That's right, and here it is.
- Come make my hands filthy.

204
00:12:39,020 --> 00:12:41,403
Say, how about something on the nose
of Letonia tomorrow?

205
00:12:41,404 --> 00:12:42,899
Uh-uh, I'm blowing this.

206
00:12:42,904 --> 00:12:46,215
I got a three-horse parlay that looks
like anybody's money. It pays 55 per 10.

207
00:12:46,216 --> 00:12:48,316
- 55, huh?
- And it's a sure thing.

208
00:12:48,355 --> 00:12:51,200
The last time Buddy played a sure
thing I had to pay all the room...

209
00:12:51,201 --> 00:12:52,281
Aw, forget that.

210
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:55,083
You oughta come in on this thing too, fella.
It's tips like this that make a fella rich.

211
00:12:55,084 --> 00:12:57,450
No thanks, I'll save my money
and stay poor.

212
00:12:57,671 --> 00:13:01,074
Alright, it's up to you. This one can't miss,
Bud, I got inside info on it.

213
00:13:01,175 --> 00:13:03,259
I know, straight from the
horse himself.

214
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:07,700
Say, Bud, if I was you, I'd sink
the whole 38 smacks on this streak.

215
00:13:07,701 --> 00:13:10,780
- Let me see, 38, that'd pay me...
- 210.

216
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:13,000
210, that's right, can you
imagine it? 210!

217
00:13:13,023 --> 00:13:14,883
That's a lot of money to make
without lifting a finger.

218
00:13:14,884 --> 00:13:16,600
Yeah, well it's a lot to lose too.

219
00:13:16,624 --> 00:13:19,980
I won't lose, I told you I was hitting
a lucky streak and this is it, I feel it.

220
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,500
- How much will it be, the whole works?
- Yeah.

221
00:13:21,501 --> 00:13:23,800
Well, how about the silk
shirt and my tie?

222
00:13:23,821 --> 00:13:27,200
Tomorrow night I'll buy you a dozen
ties, I'll dress you in ties, I'll...

223
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:34,835
Say, wait. I just remembered something.

224
00:13:34,936 --> 00:13:37,200
I can't play anything
on the ponies this time.

225
00:13:37,201 --> 00:13:39,101
- Well, what's the matter now?
- Nothing, it's just that...

226
00:13:39,102 --> 00:13:41,372
...I got something else I gotta
do with this jack.

227
00:13:41,552 --> 00:13:43,900
Well, what more can you do with it
than make it grow five times?

228
00:13:43,924 --> 00:13:46,159
Now, this is how that parlay shapes up.
In the second place...

229
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:48,040
Nope, no, I ain't gonna play it.

230
00:13:48,060 --> 00:13:50,100
See me tomorrow and maybe I'll lay
something on them then.

231
00:13:50,223 --> 00:13:52,800
Alright, it's up to you.
It's your loss.

232
00:13:52,801 --> 00:13:54,201
Don't forget what I told you.

233
00:13:56,027 --> 00:13:59,983
I'm certainly glad you've decided to
quit playing Santa Claus to them bookies.

234
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,400
- Now, if you sock that dough away, you...
- Look, John.

235
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:05,078
You hang around here till Annie
and the girlfriend get here,

236
00:14:05,079 --> 00:14:06,600
and you tell them that, er...

237
00:14:06,623 --> 00:14:09,900
Tell I was here, see, and I, er...
I got took sick kinda suddenlike...

238
00:14:09,901 --> 00:14:11,200
...and I had to go home, see?

239
00:14:11,229 --> 00:14:13,255
What'll I tell them that for?

240
00:14:16,933 --> 00:14:19,643
Oh, no, Bud, I can't do...

241
00:14:19,944 --> 00:14:22,014
Well, there goes the 38.

242
00:14:29,939 --> 00:14:32,349
- Hi, girls.
- We don't know you.

243
00:14:32,370 --> 00:14:35,227
Oh yes, you do. I'm the guy
who just said hello to you.

244
00:14:35,328 --> 00:14:37,856
You got anything special
on for tonight?

245
00:14:37,957 --> 00:14:40,333
Yeah, we were just gonna get
a bite to eat at the Astor.

246
00:14:40,354 --> 00:14:44,421
Come off, come off, you got the Astor mixed
up with the Owl Dining Car, ain't you?

247
00:14:44,622 --> 00:14:47,326
- The Owl ain't so bad at that.
- You said it.

248
00:14:47,427 --> 00:14:50,447
How about letting me sit across from you
and squirt grapefruit in your eye?

249
00:14:50,448 --> 00:14:51,800
Like they do in the movies.

250
00:14:51,848 --> 00:14:54,200
- I ain't particular.
- That goes double for me.

251
00:14:54,201 --> 00:14:57,300
Now remember, don't try to pull
no Astor stunts on me.

252
00:14:57,333 --> 00:14:59,264
I don't come from the Bronx.

253
00:14:59,265 --> 00:15:02,435
A couple of drinks in a speak, dance
and maybe a movie.

254
00:15:02,536 --> 00:15:05,550
A little party afterwards.
That's the program for the evening.

255
00:15:05,605 --> 00:15:08,390
- Are you on?
- My name's written over everything you said.

256
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,587
- Atta baby.
- Hey!

257
00:15:10,588 --> 00:15:13,488
Who's the smiley lieutenant
down there?

258
00:15:15,232 --> 00:15:19,200
He's got a little business to attend
to first then he's going to join us.

259
00:15:20,963 --> 00:15:23,074
I'll be right back.

260
00:15:24,892 --> 00:15:27,362
Well, looks like we eat.

261
00:15:27,706 --> 00:15:29,178
Boy, it's all fixed.

262
00:15:29,199 --> 00:15:31,449
Say, Bud, I don't want to go anywhere
with those two tomatoes.

263
00:15:31,469 --> 00:15:33,380
Why not?
- I won't be able to shake Annie...

264
00:15:33,381 --> 00:15:34,600
...and that other dame.

265
00:15:34,729 --> 00:15:37,780
And I ain't playing no papa to
two girls, I ain't no Turk.

266
00:15:37,804 --> 00:15:39,100
Ah, you can lose them.

267
00:15:39,127 --> 00:15:42,521
Look, if you get into a jam with them,
tell them you gotta make a phone call, see?

268
00:15:42,522 --> 00:15:45,500
Then step into some corner drugstore,
and while they're waiting outside...

269
00:15:45,550 --> 00:15:48,354
you sneak out the side door, get it?

270
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,200
Hey, what's holding up the party?

271
00:15:50,227 --> 00:15:52,800
Just giving the boyfriend a few tips
on the love racket.

272
00:15:52,891 --> 00:15:55,600
If he's that green, what kind
of an evening am I going to have?

273
00:15:55,711 --> 00:15:58,373
- Bud, here she comes now.
- Who?

274
00:15:58,374 --> 00:15:59,374
Annie.

275
00:16:02,660 --> 00:16:05,500
- Look who she's brought with her.
- The firewagon.

276
00:16:05,527 --> 00:16:07,500
Say, I thought you told her...
I'm gonna beat it!

277
00:16:07,556 --> 00:16:09,980
Look, John, you can't do that.
What am I going to do with the girls?

278
00:16:10,005 --> 00:16:12,700
Push them off the pier. I ain't gonna
play fireman again tonight.

279
00:16:16,183 --> 00:16:18,600
I'm sorry but the heavy sugar's
coming down the street.

280
00:16:18,625 --> 00:16:20,200
- The party's off.
- It's off?

281
00:16:20,220 --> 00:16:23,127
That's a hot way to treat
a couple of ladies.

282
00:16:23,128 --> 00:16:25,400
Well, looks like we don't eat.

283
00:16:26,828 --> 00:16:28,650
- Hello, honey.
- Hello, Bud.

284
00:16:28,951 --> 00:16:30,751
What's the idea?

285
00:16:30,752 --> 00:16:33,152
- What's the matter with her?
- I thought you said the laundry.

286
00:16:33,153 --> 00:16:36,353
- Listen, she's the best I could do.
- I don't believe you.

287
00:16:36,354 --> 00:16:38,254
I think you're trying to put
something over on me again.

288
00:16:38,255 --> 00:16:39,255
Where's the boyfriend?

289
00:16:39,256 --> 00:16:42,150
He ain't here and he ain't never
going to be here.

290
00:16:42,151 --> 00:16:43,901
- What's the matter?
- He's sick.

291
00:16:43,902 --> 00:16:46,600
- When did all this happen?
- I'll talk to you later.

292
00:16:46,601 --> 00:16:50,451
- Ain't I going to have a boyfriend tonight?
- Not unless you go down to the firehouse.

293
00:16:50,452 --> 00:16:52,100
Firehouse, what for?

294
00:16:52,101 --> 00:16:54,000
What's the use of us standing
around chinning?

295
00:16:54,001 --> 00:16:56,601
- Ain't we going anyplace?
- Yeah, I feel hungry.

296
00:16:56,602 --> 00:16:58,402
Yeah, we're going someplace.

297
00:16:58,403 --> 00:17:01,800
- We're going down to a drugstore.
- Drugstore? What for?

298
00:17:01,824 --> 00:17:03,904
I gotta make a phone call.

299
00:17:33,005 --> 00:17:35,705
- Hey, what's the matter with you?
- Say, where do you think you are, home?

300
00:17:35,706 --> 00:17:38,500
- This is a dance hall, ain't it?
- Sure it's a dance hall, and that's all it is.

301
00:17:38,501 --> 00:17:41,601
I got a right to dance and you
gotta dance with me, I paid for it.

302
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:43,702
You pay to dance with your feet,
not your hands.

303
00:17:43,703 --> 00:17:45,600
I dance my own way, come on.

304
00:17:45,601 --> 00:17:47,201
And I dance my way.

305
00:17:48,002 --> 00:17:49,302
Say, what's the matter here?

306
00:17:49,303 --> 00:17:53,400
Ask him. He just bought the place.
Paid a dime for it.

307
00:17:53,401 --> 00:17:56,000
I paid a dime for you and I want
a nickel change.

308
00:17:56,001 --> 00:17:57,300
What's happened, brother?

309
00:17:57,301 --> 00:17:59,171
Oh, I tried to dance with
the girl nice and...

310
00:17:59,172 --> 00:18:00,972
Come on, sure, I'll fix you out.

311
00:18:38,373 --> 00:18:41,373
Alright now, let's forget about it,
Shirley, come on, get in line.

312
00:18:41,374 --> 00:18:42,664
Atta girl.

313
00:18:47,474 --> 00:18:49,174
I want one ticket.

314
00:18:53,075 --> 00:18:54,675
Alright, right this way, brother.

315
00:18:54,676 --> 00:18:56,676
Yes, there are nice girls all over.

316
00:19:00,477 --> 00:19:03,077
Here you are, Shirley, here's a nice
fellow for you. Dance with him.

317
00:19:20,678 --> 00:19:23,778
Say, big boy, you sure are
a swell little hoofer.

318
00:19:23,879 --> 00:19:26,179
You ain't so bad yourself.

319
00:19:26,580 --> 00:19:29,999
I'll improve, if only I can get
some practice.

320
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,400
Say, um...

321
00:19:33,501 --> 00:19:37,901
Do you girls have to dance with
everybody who has a ticket?

322
00:19:37,902 --> 00:19:39,152
Why not?

323
00:19:39,153 --> 00:19:43,853
Well, it must be sort of tough letting
every guy paw you.

324
00:19:43,854 --> 00:19:47,500
They don't paw me, not if they know
what's good for them.

325
00:19:47,501 --> 00:19:50,901
Yeah, I guess you do learn
to take care of yourself.

326
00:19:53,902 --> 00:19:55,900
Is this your first time up here?

327
00:19:55,901 --> 00:19:57,301
Yeah.

328
00:19:58,302 --> 00:20:01,000
I came up here by accident.

329
00:20:01,701 --> 00:20:03,801
A big accident.

330
00:20:03,802 --> 00:20:05,502
What's the gag?

331
00:20:05,503 --> 00:20:08,903
Oh, you wouldn't understand.
It ain't important anyway.

332
00:20:13,404 --> 00:20:18,900
You know... you don't seem like
these other girls.

333
00:20:18,901 --> 00:20:21,601
You seem more refined like.

334
00:20:21,602 --> 00:20:23,802
Go ahead, where's the rest of it?

335
00:20:23,803 --> 00:20:25,803
- Rest of what?
- The story.

336
00:20:25,804 --> 00:20:29,904
I'm different. I don't belong here,
and you're gonna take me out of it.

337
00:20:29,905 --> 00:20:32,105
No, I'm not, why should I?

338
00:20:32,806 --> 00:20:34,696
Don't you want to put me
in a show?

339
00:20:34,697 --> 00:20:37,497
Ain't you got a friend that knows
a big producer?

340
00:20:37,498 --> 00:20:41,098
- Not me.
- You're the first guy that ain't then.

341
00:20:42,499 --> 00:20:44,899
Say, do they all try to pull
that stuff on you?

342
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:48,900
All. Except the ones that try the little
apartment on the avenue line.

343
00:20:48,901 --> 00:20:51,101
Well, you wouldn't fall for that
sort of thing, would you?

344
00:20:51,102 --> 00:20:53,302
I'm still here, ain't I?

345
00:20:54,303 --> 00:20:56,003
Not that I'm going to stay here.

346
00:20:56,004 --> 00:20:58,904
I got ambition. And someday
I'm gonna get them, see?

347
00:20:59,605 --> 00:21:01,405
I hope you do.

348
00:21:04,406 --> 00:21:07,206
Well, how about the next one?

349
00:21:07,207 --> 00:21:10,207
- I'm willing.
- Where's your ticket?

350
00:21:10,208 --> 00:21:12,408
Well... I only got one.

351
00:21:12,409 --> 00:21:14,909
Do you know any more Scotch stories?

352
00:21:15,810 --> 00:21:19,010
Come on, let's dance it out anyway
and I'll get a ticket later.

353
00:21:19,030 --> 00:21:20,480
I can't. Gotta have a ticket.

354
00:21:20,481 --> 00:21:23,481
Well, you wait here for me
and I'll go get one.

355
00:21:23,482 --> 00:21:27,282
Get a handful of them so's we can
dance a lot together.

356
00:21:27,283 --> 00:21:28,683
Huh?

357
00:21:29,384 --> 00:21:31,000
Alright.

358
00:21:47,601 --> 00:21:51,101
- How about this one, baby?
- I'm waiting for a guy.

359
00:21:51,102 --> 00:21:53,702
Yeah? Since when are you
reserving him?

360
00:21:55,303 --> 00:21:58,103
Oh, alright. You needn't get
sore about it.

361
00:22:10,704 --> 00:22:12,804
Say, where's the blond girl
that was here?

362
00:22:12,805 --> 00:22:15,905
She's out dancing. Dance with me.

363
00:22:15,906 --> 00:22:18,106
No, thanks, I'll wait.

364
00:22:30,707 --> 00:22:32,507
- Hey!
- Fresh guy, huh?

365
00:22:32,508 --> 00:22:34,008
What's the matter here,
what's the matter?

366
00:22:34,009 --> 00:22:36,000
You try that again and I'll
break your neck!

367
00:22:36,001 --> 00:22:37,001
More trouble.

368
00:22:37,002 --> 00:22:40,280
Just because he paid a dime to dance with
me he thinks that entitles him to privileges.

369
00:22:40,281 --> 00:22:42,600
Oh, who wants any
privileges with you?

370
00:22:42,601 --> 00:22:45,600
A dime would be too much for
a bimbo like you!

371
00:22:47,001 --> 00:22:49,001
What are you trying to do,
wreck this place?

372
00:22:49,002 --> 00:22:51,322
You get your things, Shirley,
and clear out. And stay out.

373
00:22:51,323 --> 00:22:53,663
Now wait a minute. You don't have
to take it out on her.

374
00:22:53,664 --> 00:22:55,624
This is between me and that guy.

375
00:22:55,625 --> 00:22:57,375
Yeah, well I ain't going to argue
with her or with you, see?

376
00:22:57,376 --> 00:22:59,376
Get out of here both of you
before the cops come!

377
00:22:59,377 --> 00:23:01,400
Here, take him in the back room.

378
00:23:01,401 --> 00:23:04,400
Well, what are you all standing around for?
Come on, enjoy yourselves.

379
00:23:04,401 --> 00:23:06,901
Everybody dance, music, music!

380
00:23:29,202 --> 00:23:31,802
It was wonderful of you to stick up
for me the way you did.

381
00:23:31,803 --> 00:23:35,103
Oh, that was nothing. That guy
was just aching for a sock.

382
00:23:35,104 --> 00:23:36,804
And he sure got it.

383
00:23:37,105 --> 00:23:41,485
Gee, I never thought anybody would think
enough about me to stand up for me that way.

384
00:23:41,486 --> 00:23:43,586
Oh, I would have done
the same for any girl.

385
00:23:43,587 --> 00:23:46,287
- Oh... I thought...
- What?

386
00:23:47,088 --> 00:23:48,688
Nothing.

387
00:23:49,089 --> 00:23:52,189
Say, do you know...
That's what's the trouble with your job.

388
00:23:52,490 --> 00:23:54,440
You know, it makes the guy
think you're...

389
00:23:54,941 --> 00:23:57,041
Well, what he said you were.

390
00:23:57,642 --> 00:24:00,742
You hadn't ought to work
there anymore.

391
00:24:00,743 --> 00:24:02,443
I don't.

392
00:24:02,444 --> 00:24:04,944
Gee, and it was my fault
you got canned.

393
00:24:04,945 --> 00:24:08,145
Oh, no! Nothing would have happened
if I hadn't slapped him myself.

394
00:24:08,146 --> 00:24:11,146
But then I couldn't let him play
around with me that way, could I?

395
00:24:11,147 --> 00:24:15,047
- No, not if you're decent.
- Well, that's one thing I am.

396
00:24:15,048 --> 00:24:18,848
And they work in a tough joint, but everybody
that knows me knows I'm on the level.

397
00:24:18,849 --> 00:24:21,549
Well, that's the only way
for a girl to be.

398
00:24:23,150 --> 00:24:27,450
But why, why do you work
in a dump like that?

399
00:24:27,451 --> 00:24:30,100
Because I can make more money
that way than any other business.

400
00:24:30,101 --> 00:24:33,901
You see, I got a family
to take care of.

401
00:24:33,902 --> 00:24:36,202
My mother and father, I mean.

402
00:24:36,203 --> 00:24:37,503
Oh.

403
00:24:37,804 --> 00:24:40,004
They're both sick.

404
00:24:40,005 --> 00:24:42,305
I keep them on a farm in Idaho.

405
00:24:42,806 --> 00:24:44,556
You're not handing me a line,
are you?

406
00:24:44,557 --> 00:24:46,027
Alright, if that's what you think!

407
00:24:46,028 --> 00:24:48,028
No, no, only it sounds like,
you know...

408
00:24:48,029 --> 00:24:49,629
It's the truth, that's all.

409
00:24:49,630 --> 00:24:53,630
Yeah... Well, what are you
going to do now?

410
00:24:53,631 --> 00:24:55,431
I don't know.

411
00:24:55,432 --> 00:24:57,800
Gee, I get kind of scared when
I think about being all alone...

412
00:24:57,801 --> 00:24:59,541
...in New York without any money.

413
00:25:00,442 --> 00:25:02,000
Yeah.

414
00:25:02,001 --> 00:25:04,501
What do you do for a living?

415
00:25:04,502 --> 00:25:06,602
Oh, I'm a riveter.

416
00:25:06,603 --> 00:25:09,103
That's where you get such
a big muscle, ain't it?

417
00:25:09,104 --> 00:25:10,404
Yeah.

418
00:25:11,405 --> 00:25:13,505
You make good money
at it too, don't you?

419
00:25:13,506 --> 00:25:15,306
Sixty-two fifty per.

420
00:25:15,307 --> 00:25:17,457
Boy, you and Rockefeller.

421
00:25:17,458 --> 00:25:20,758
Yeah. You know, that's more than
most college professors make.

422
00:25:20,759 --> 00:25:24,059
- Or so my buddy says.
- I'll bet he's right.

423
00:25:24,060 --> 00:25:26,100
The fellows that put up these
big steel skyscrapers...

424
00:25:26,101 --> 00:25:28,461
...are more important than any
college professor.

425
00:25:28,462 --> 00:25:30,862
Oh, no, I wouldn't say that.

426
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:33,773
I think education is the biggest
thing in the world.

427
00:25:33,774 --> 00:25:37,000
Not that I'm against education.
I got a good one myself.

428
00:25:37,001 --> 00:25:40,301
- You have?
- Yeah, I went a year to high school.

429
00:25:40,302 --> 00:25:43,382
- No kidding.
- I wish I could have stuck it out but...

430
00:25:43,383 --> 00:25:46,583
Like I told you, the folks were sick
and I had to help them.

431
00:25:46,584 --> 00:25:49,084
Yeah, well that sure is tough.

432
00:25:49,785 --> 00:25:52,885
You know, I haven't learned any myself.

433
00:25:53,586 --> 00:25:55,286
I wish I had.

434
00:25:56,287 --> 00:25:58,166
Do you know what I was
planning on doing?

435
00:25:58,167 --> 00:25:59,800
Before I lost my job, I mean.

436
00:25:59,801 --> 00:26:01,481
I got ambition, see?

437
00:26:01,482 --> 00:26:04,982
And I was planning on...
on going to some business college...

438
00:26:04,983 --> 00:26:06,883
...and finishing my education that way.

439
00:26:06,884 --> 00:26:07,884
You were?

440
00:26:07,885 --> 00:26:10,385
Yeah, that's why I was glad
I worked nights.

441
00:26:10,386 --> 00:26:12,200
It gave me the daytime to study.

442
00:26:12,201 --> 00:26:15,541
But, gee, now that I'm out of work...

443
00:26:15,542 --> 00:26:18,900
Hey, my Buddy's girl, Annie...

444
00:26:18,901 --> 00:26:21,801
See, she works in the paper box factory.

445
00:26:21,802 --> 00:26:24,582
Maybe I could get her to speak
to her boss about taking you on.

446
00:26:24,583 --> 00:26:27,083
Oh, no, that wouldn't give me
time to study.

447
00:26:27,684 --> 00:26:31,984
Never mind. I'll speak to Tony myself.
I'm sure he'll take me on again.

448
00:26:31,985 --> 00:26:33,800
Oh, no, no. Say, that would
give all those fellows...

449
00:26:33,801 --> 00:26:35,600
...a chance to get fresh
with you again.

450
00:26:35,601 --> 00:26:37,201
It'll only be for a short time.

451
00:26:37,202 --> 00:26:40,402
It sure is tough on a
pretty girl, ain't it?

452
00:26:40,403 --> 00:26:42,503
Do you really think I'm pretty?

453
00:26:43,804 --> 00:26:47,104
- Why, yeah!
- I'm glad you think so.

454
00:26:48,705 --> 00:26:51,405
It's the first time I ever heard a fellow
say it that I was glad he did.

455
00:26:51,406 --> 00:26:53,806
- Yeah?
- Yeah!

456
00:26:54,707 --> 00:26:58,207
Oh but, I guess at that I won't be
seeing you anymore, will I?

457
00:26:58,208 --> 00:27:01,808
Oh, I don't know.
I haven't thought about it.

458
00:27:01,809 --> 00:27:03,909
But you want to?

459
00:27:03,910 --> 00:27:07,710
Why, yes, I guess so.

460
00:27:07,711 --> 00:27:11,111
It'll make it so much easier for me.
At the dance hall, I mean.

461
00:27:11,112 --> 00:27:12,412
- Yeah?
- If the fellows knew...

462
00:27:12,413 --> 00:27:15,680
...I had a big guy like you looking out for
me, they wouldn't try and get fresh then.

463
00:27:15,681 --> 00:27:17,681
Yeah, I bet you they wouldn't, huh?

464
00:27:19,282 --> 00:27:20,880
And then, when I was studying,

465
00:27:20,881 --> 00:27:22,971
there'd be lots of times I wouldn't know
what things meant.

466
00:27:22,972 --> 00:27:25,172
I won't have anybody to ask.

467
00:27:25,173 --> 00:27:30,473
- But if you was around.
- Oh, no, no I couldn't help you that way.

468
00:27:30,474 --> 00:27:34,200
You know, I don't know
anything about books.

469
00:27:34,201 --> 00:27:37,501
I'll bet you do.
But even if you don't...

470
00:27:37,502 --> 00:27:39,702
...we could study them out together.

471
00:27:39,703 --> 00:27:41,600
That's what we could do.

472
00:27:42,501 --> 00:27:44,200
Yeah?

473
00:27:46,002 --> 00:27:48,302
Say, that would be something like.

474
00:27:48,303 --> 00:27:51,303
That's what I'd like awful much to do
if you let me, mister...

475
00:27:52,104 --> 00:27:55,500
- John Allen's the name.
- Shirley Day's mine.

476
00:27:56,101 --> 00:27:59,101
Well, I'm certainly glad
to meet you, Miss Day.

477
00:27:59,102 --> 00:28:02,302
And I sure am glad to
meet you, Mr. Allen.

478
00:28:03,503 --> 00:28:05,203
Well.

479
00:28:07,104 --> 00:28:08,404
Yeah.

480
00:28:08,405 --> 00:28:10,335
She's got you dizzy, that's what.

481
00:28:10,336 --> 00:28:12,636
I thought you had more sense
than fall for the first dame...

482
00:28:12,637 --> 00:28:15,337
...that sighs at you and tells you
how wonderful you are.

483
00:28:15,338 --> 00:28:17,988
Here me and Annie's been chasing
around trying to get you interested...

484
00:28:17,989 --> 00:28:21,300
...in some nice little home girl.
But no, this one's too fat,

485
00:28:21,301 --> 00:28:23,101
this one worked in a laundry.

486
00:28:24,002 --> 00:28:27,880
While we go chasing around trying to find
a Peggy Joyce for you, what do you do?

487
00:28:27,901 --> 00:28:31,101
You go out and get yourself
hard-tied by a dance-hall Jane.

488
00:28:31,102 --> 00:28:34,302
You was the guy that didn't have
no use for women.

489
00:28:34,303 --> 00:28:38,000
They was all flies, and you got such
a big laugh looking down on them.

490
00:28:38,001 --> 00:28:41,900
- Yeah, but I get a big kick out of Shirley.
- Ah, you could do better with a mule.

491
00:28:41,901 --> 00:28:44,101
You think I'm stuck on her,
but I ain't.

492
00:28:44,102 --> 00:28:46,502
I got my eyes open,
I know what I'm doing.

493
00:28:46,503 --> 00:28:48,400
But do you know what she's doing?

494
00:28:48,401 --> 00:28:49,700
That's what counts.

495
00:28:49,701 --> 00:28:51,380
She ain't after nothing from me.

496
00:28:51,381 --> 00:28:54,681
Oh, no, she's sweet, and pure,
and innocent.

497
00:28:54,682 --> 00:28:58,082
- She really is on the level.
- Don't make me laugh.

498
00:28:58,083 --> 00:29:00,700
- How much has she got out of you so far?
- Not a red cent.

499
00:29:00,701 --> 00:29:03,980
- Have you offered her any?
- Oh, just before she got her job back,

500
