afraid of him, John.

585
00:33:40,103 --> 00:33:42,303
What's the matter with him?

586
00:33:42,304 --> 00:33:44,404
I don't like the way he looks at me.

587
00:33:45,905 --> 00:33:48,405
What way does he look at you?

588
00:33:48,406 --> 00:33:50,606
Oh... you know.

589
00:33:52,007 --> 00:33:53,307
Ahh!

590
00:33:53,308 --> 00:33:56,008
Hey there! Another cup of tea.

591
00:33:56,009 --> 00:33:58,409
- And bring the bottle this time.
- Yes, ma'am.

592
00:33:58,410 --> 00:34:01,110
No more for me.

593
00:34:17,411 --> 00:34:19,811
Leave the bottle, I said!

594
00:34:24,512 --> 00:34:26,712
Come on, come on, let's go to
that lecture.

595
00:34:26,713 --> 00:34:30,253
- Not yet, honey.
- But you said you would.

596
00:34:30,254 --> 00:34:32,254
I wanna see the manager first.

597
00:34:32,255 --> 00:34:34,655
- What for?
- To see if he won't take me on.

598
00:34:34,656 --> 00:34:39,756
You don't want to take a job
dancing here like that, would you?

599
00:34:39,757 --> 00:34:42,000
Half undressed.

600
00:34:42,001 --> 00:34:44,101
Wouldn't you want me to?

601
00:34:44,902 --> 00:34:47,602
What difference would it make to me?

602
00:34:47,603 --> 00:34:50,000
Wouldn't it make just a little
bit of difference?

603
00:34:51,201 --> 00:34:53,101
Now look here, Shirley.

604
00:34:53,302 --> 00:34:56,502
- I like you a whole lot, see?
- Yeah?

605
00:34:57,203 --> 00:34:59,203
And that's all.

606
00:34:59,204 --> 00:35:01,504
That's as far as it goes.

607
00:35:01,505 --> 00:35:03,205
Oh, John!

608
00:35:04,706 --> 00:35:07,800
Oh, come on, don't start that again.

609
00:35:07,801 --> 00:35:11,000
I can't stand it, not when I'm drunk.

610
00:35:13,401 --> 00:35:14,701
You know...

611
00:35:15,902 --> 00:35:18,202
I think I'm a little drunk.

612
00:35:18,203 --> 00:35:21,683
Oh, John, be nice to me.

613
00:35:21,684 --> 00:35:25,184
- I'm so lonely.
- Alright, alright, I'll be nice.

614
00:35:25,185 --> 00:35:27,585
Oh, John!

615
00:35:30,786 --> 00:35:33,586
Hey... you know, I like that.

616
00:35:33,587 --> 00:35:38,387
- Wouldn't you like to have more?
- That ain't a bad idea.

617
00:35:39,788 --> 00:35:44,988
No... I don't want any more.

618
00:35:46,189 --> 00:35:48,289
I don't want anything.

619
00:35:50,290 --> 00:35:52,190
Now look here, Shirley.

620
00:35:53,091 --> 00:35:57,591
You're a good kid, see, a good kid.

621
00:35:59,292 --> 00:36:02,000
But you ain't for me.

622
00:36:02,001 --> 00:36:04,001
That's a nice thing to say.

623
00:36:04,002 --> 00:36:06,902
Alright, it doesn't matter.

624
00:36:07,903 --> 00:36:09,703
I know you don't care
a rap about me.

625
00:36:09,704 --> 00:36:13,000
Sure I do, Shirley, I care
about you a whole lot.

626
00:36:13,001 --> 00:36:16,200
- I said I did.
- You never kissed me.

627
00:36:16,201 --> 00:36:19,601
I did. Just a while ago.

628
00:36:19,602 --> 00:36:22,332
I don't mean like that.
I mean kissing me because you must do it!

629
00:36:22,333 --> 00:36:23,888
Because you can't keep yourself back.

630
00:36:23,889 --> 00:36:26,500
Because your whole inside
burns up just for me.

631
00:36:26,501 --> 00:36:30,201
- Oh, shush...
- That's how I am for you.

632
00:36:34,402 --> 00:36:36,302
- Shirley...
- Yes, John?

633
00:36:36,303 --> 00:36:38,203
I know what you mean.

634
00:36:39,004 --> 00:36:41,804
Yeah, that's how I want you now.

635
00:36:41,805 --> 00:36:45,200
- No, John, you don't love me.
- Yes, I do. I do, Shirley.

636
