00:40:05,406 --> 00:40:07,986
I ain't gonna let you pull your
old army game in him.

692
00:40:07,987 --> 00:40:10,887
- Who's pulling the army game?
- You are and you know it.

693
00:40:10,888 --> 00:40:14,090
You got him drunk so's he'd get all hot over
you and now you're framing him to marry you.

694
00:40:14,091 --> 00:40:17,081
I don't have to frame anything,
Mr. Wise-guy.

695
00:40:17,082 --> 00:40:19,082
We're married already.

696
00:40:19,083 --> 00:40:20,683
You're what?

697
00:40:22,084 --> 00:40:24,784
- John! John!
- What's the matter now?

698
00:40:24,785 --> 00:40:26,800
Did you let this dirty little egg
rope you in?

699
00:40:26,801 --> 00:40:28,801
Hey, that's no way to talk
about his wife!

700
00:40:28,802 --> 00:40:32,402
- You filthy little rat you!
- What's the matter now?

701
00:40:32,403 --> 00:40:36,903
I can't stay here any longer.
I gotta take her to that lecture.

702
00:40:36,904 --> 00:40:39,704
- Come on, John.
- That's all I'm gonna do.

703
00:40:39,805 --> 00:40:43,705
There ain't a chance she's
taking me for a ride.

704
00:40:43,706 --> 00:40:48,106
- I'm just a little bit too smart for her.
- Take it easy now, will you?

705
00:40:50,507 --> 00:40:52,437
I ain't gonna let you get
away with this.

706
00:40:52,438 --> 00:40:55,600
Oh, what are you sore about anyway?
I ain't taking nothing away from you.

707
00:40:55,601 --> 00:40:58,090
He ain't the kind of man you're
used to playing around with.

708
00:40:58,091 --> 00:41:00,051
- He's s square shooter.
- Well, ain't I?

709
00:41:00,052 --> 00:41:03,152
Yeah, I know your kind.
And so do lots of other guys I'll bet.

710
00:41:03,153 --> 00:41:05,853
Only they was all too smart to let you
ring the wedding bells on them.

711
00:41:05,854 --> 00:41:10,100
But this poor guy. Didn't take you long
to find out he couldn't hold his liquor.

712
00:41:10,101 --> 00:41:11,201
Say listen, brother.

713
00:41:11,202 --> 00:41:13,702
Until you can talk the signature
off of this...

714
00:41:13,703 --> 00:41:16,700
you're only wasting your breath
making nasty cracks about me.

715
00:41:16,701 --> 00:41:18,999
Hm, you got a license and everything, eh?

716
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:22,200
How much did you have to pay extra to
get this at night? And got him drunk, too.

717
00:41:22,211 --> 00:41:25,100
He wasn't drunk when I got it,
he was perfectly sober.

718
00:41:25,101 --> 00:41:28,301
But he wanted to celebrate our wedding.
That's how he got tanked up.

719
00:41:28,302 --> 00:41:29,902
I don't believe you.

720
00:41:29,903 --> 00:41:31,803
I notice you ain't let up none.

721
00:41:31,804 --> 00:41:35,280
No, you had to keep your head clear so
you could steer him into this, didn't you?

722
00:41:35,281 --> 00:41:38,000
He's a little white angel, ain't he?
It's me that's all bad, eh?

723
00:41:38,001 --> 00:41:40,751
The worst thing you ever did
was getting born.

724
00:41:40,752 --> 00:41:42,020
It's a good thing he's passed out.

725
00:41:42,021 --> 00:41:43,800
If he was sober, you wouldn't
dare insult me like this.

726
00:41:43,801 --> 00:41:45,901
If he was sober you wouldn't
be here like this!

727
00:41:46,802 --> 00:41:49,332
Oh, it's all over, ain't it?

728
00:41:49,333 --> 00:41:51,463
I'll be good to him, honest I will.

729
00:41:51,464 --> 00:41:54,064
- He won't ever be sorry he married me.
- No.

730
00:41:55,365 --> 00:41:58,665
Come on, let's you and me
be friends too.

731
00:41:58,666 --> 00:41:59,999
Not me!

732
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:02,900
If he had taken you because
he wanted to, I wouldn't interfere.

733
00:42:02,901 --> 00:42:05,980
Since you put this over on him with
your cheap dirty tricks,

734
00:42:05,981 --> 00:42:07,000
I ain't gonna let you get away with it?

735
00:42:07,001 --> 00:42:09,601
Alright then, you've had your say
now listen to mine!

736
00:42:09,602 --> 00:42:12,900
He's married to me, right,
square and legal.

737
00:42:12,901 --> 00:42:15,201
And since I'm his wife and partner
to all that's his,

738
00:42:15,202 --> 00:42:17,402
you just get out of here, see?

739
00:42:18,903 --> 00:42:21,403
My husband's waiting for me.

740
00:42:21,404 --> 00:42:23,604
And I ain't gonna keep him waiting.

741
00:42:33,305 --> 00:42:36,300
Alright, I'll get out.

742
00:42:36,301 --> 00:42:38,001
But get this.

743
00:42:38,002 --> 00:42:40,602
I'll make you sorry for what
you've done to him.

744
00:42:47,503 --> 00:42:51,000
You said you'd bring me home
a lollipop, big boy.

745
00:42:51,701 --> 00:42:55,600
And you did alright.
And a red one at that.

746
00:43:07,001 --> 00:43:09,601
Welcome home, Shirley.

747
00:43:32,202 --> 00:43:33,902
Cigarette?

748
00:43:33,903 --> 00:43:36,703
Oh, Bud, how long are you
gonna keep sore at me?

749
00:43:37,904 --> 00:43:39,184
- I ain't sore at you.
- Yes, you are.

750
00:43:39,185 --> 00:43:40,600
You've been this way ever
since the night I...

751
00:43:40,601 --> 00:43:42,701
- Do you blame me?
- Well, it's my funeral ain't it?

752
00:43:42,702 --> 00:43:44,002
Only because you won't
listen to me.

753
00:43:44,003 --> 00:43:46,803
I can't, I gotta play square.
After all I married her.

754
00:43:46,804 --> 00:43:49,904
Yeah, when you were so cockeyed drunk
you didn't know what you was doing.

755
00:43:49,905 --> 00:43:53,145
Well, whether I was drunk or sober I'm
married to her now, see, and I gotta stick.

756
00:43:53,146 --> 00:43:55,006
No, you ain't. I ain't gonna let you.

757
00:43:55,007 --> 00:43:57,407
- Why not?
- 'Cause you're too good to be tied to her.

758
00:43:57,408 --> 00:43:59,508
- Maybe I wanna be.
- Oh, no you don't.

759
00:43:59,509 --> 00:44:03,209
It's only because you're so fine that
you don't want to do anything to hurt her.

760
00:44:03,210 --> 00:44:06,410
But I ain't fine, see?
And I ain't afraid to hurt her.

761
00:44:06,411 --> 00:44:09,311
I can't walk out on her if that's what
you're after. It wouldn't be fair.

762
00:44:09,312 --> 00:44:11,712
I know her kind. She's a softy.

763
00:44:11,713 --> 00:44:13,353
She got tired of grubbing
for her own keep,

764
00:44:13,354 --> 00:44:16,154
you look like three squares and
flop to her so she hooked you.

765
00:44:16,155 --> 00:44:17,700
I don't think so.

766
00:44:17,701 --> 00:44:19,700
You've only been married
to her three weeks.

767
00:44:19,701 --> 00:44:21,901
Where's all that dough
you had in the bank?

768
00:44:21,902 --> 00:44:23,600
On her back already, ain't it?

769
00:44:23,601 --> 00:44:24,881
She had to have decent clothes.

770
00:44:24,882 --> 00:44:28,182
A riveter's wife don't need
silk lingerie and silk pajamas.

771
00:44:28,183 --> 00:44:30,383
Not a night gown, mind you, pajamas!

772
00:44:30,384 --> 00:44:31,984
That shows you what she's like.

773
00:44:33,005 --> 00:44:36,285
- More rivets!
- You'll have to wait a minute.

774
00:44:36,286 --> 00:44:41,056
Oh, Bud! Why are you so
bitter against her?

775
00:44:41,057 --> 00:44:43,200
Because I... Well...

776
00:44:43,201 --> 00:44:46,100
You're the kind of guy I wished
I could have been myself.

777
00:44:46,101 --> 00:44:48,671
That's why I'm so broke up about
this tramp getting you.

778
00:44:48,672 --> 00:44:49,672
Don't call her that.

779
00:44:49,673 --> 00:44:51,873
That's all she is. Don't you think
I know the breed?

780
00:44:51,874 --> 00:44:53,644
She lied to you about her
parents, didn't she?

781
00:44:53,645 --> 00:44:55,800
Said they was out on a farm in Idaho.

782
00:44:55,801 --> 00:44:58,501
All the time they was living in
a booze joint on 10th Ave.

783
00:44:58,502 --> 00:45:01,702
Yeah, I don't know why she lied
to me about them.

784
00:45:01,703 --> 00:45:04,000
I do. She's lied to you about
other things.

785
00:45:04,001 --> 00:45:06,301
And she'll keep on lying to you
the rest of her life.

786
00:45:06,302 --> 00:45:07,600
She was born crooked.

787
00:45:07,601 --> 00:45:09,371
It ain't in her nature to play
square with a man.

788
00:45:09,372 --> 00:45:13,100
Don't say that! She's on the level
that way, with men I mean.

789
00:45:13,101 --> 00:45:14,600
- I know she is.
- Yeah?

790
00:45:14,601 --> 00:45:17,700
Where'd she get all them glad rags
she was dolled up in when she come to you?

791
00:45:17,701 --> 00:45:21,401
From dancing?
She only made 5c a dance.

792
00:45:21,402 --> 00:45:24,000
There's a limit to how much you can make
adding up pennies in a night.

793
00:45:24,001 --> 00:45:27,900
She wouldn't have made enough to buy them
clothes not even if she was a merry-go-round.

794
00:45:27,901 --> 00:45:30,051
- She's worked hard.
- Sure she has.

795
00:45:30,052 --> 00:45:31,900
And I'll tell you where she did it too.

796
00:45:31,901 --> 00:45:34,201
The same place she still goes
every afternoon.

797
00:45:34,202 --> 00:45:36,602
- She goes to the movies.
- Yeah?

798
00:45:36,603 --> 00:45:39,480
Now look here, Bud. There's a limit
to what I'll stand for.

799
00:45:39,481 --> 00:45:42,331
- You'll stand for all I've got to give you.
- No I won't!

800
00:45:42,332 --> 00:45:45,232
What she's done before
we got married that's out, see?

801
00:45:45,233 --> 00:45:47,400
You and me haven't been
holiness ourselves.

802
00:45:47,401 --> 00:45:51,080
She's my wife now, and you and everybody
else has got to respect her.

803
00:45:51,091 --> 00:45:53,351
- Your wife? Tony's wife!
- Don't say that.

804
00:45:53,352 --> 00:45:56,002
Yes, his wife. Anybody else's wife that
wanted. I could have had her myself!

805
00:45:56,003 --> 00:45:57,500
Shut up you!

806
00:45:57,501 --> 00:45:58,801
Bud!

807
00:45:58,902 --> 00:46:00,402
Bud!

808
00:46:00,503 --> 00:46:01,803
Bud!

809
00:46:02,604 --> 00:46:04,204
Bud!

810
00:46:16,205 --> 00:46:19,200
- You gonna play that all day long?
- Why not?

811
00:46:19,201 --> 00:46:21,541
It's the only fun I can get
around here.

812
00:46:21,542 --> 00:46:23,642
You ain't no happiness boy
these days.

813
00:46:24,443 --> 00:46:27,200
You don't like me to play it
just because it was his.

814
00:46:27,801 --> 00:46:29,901
Oh, alright!

815
00:46:30,002 --> 00:46:33,222
How long are you gonna
keep on being like this?

816
00:46:33,223 --> 00:46:35,700
Makes me sick to look at you.

817
00:46:35,701 --> 00:46:37,400
Why don't you go out
and get yourself a job?

818
00:46:37,701 --> 00:46:42,000
- I can't get one. I've tried.
- You can go back to riveting.

819
00:46:42,032 --> 00:46:44,002
You know the boss would take
you on again as soon as you got better.

820
00:46:44,003 --> 00:46:46,200
No, I can't go back to that.

821
00:46:46,501 --> 00:46:48,201
Not ever since Bud...

822
00:46:48,902 --> 00:46:51,002
I can't climb.

823
00:46:51,703 --> 00:46:55,103
When I get up there...
my had swims.

824
00:46:55,704 --> 00:46:57,504
I get sick, afraid.

825
00:46:57,505 --> 00:46:59,999
- I gotta hold on.
- Oh, rats!

826
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:02,600
One minute he was standing
there talking to me.

827
00:47:02,601 --> 00:47:06,001
And the next he... he was flying
through space.

828
00:47:06,002 --> 00:47:10,202
His fingers clawing, trying to catch hold
of something and nothing for him to grab.

829
00:47:10,803 --> 00:47:12,603
And then when he hit...

830
00:47:12,604 --> 00:47:15,604
I see, well it's going to be up to me
to go back to work.

831
00:47:15,605 --> 00:47:18,505
No, you don't!
You stay right here!

832
00:47:18,506 --> 00:47:21,306
I'm going to make all the money
that comes into this house!

833
00:47:21,307 --> 00:47:22,500
Well, do it then!

834
00:47:22,501 --> 00:47:25,000
I ain't anxious to go back to the hall
and let the girls give me the laugh...

835
00:47:25,001 --> 00:47:27,441
...for marrying a guy and then
having to support him.

836
00:47:27,442 --> 00:47:29,500
You keep away from that dance hall.

837
00:47:29,501 --> 00:47:30,820
What am I supposed to be doing...

838
00:47:30,821 --> 00:47:33,100
while you're hanging on to
a hunk of steel crying...

839
00:47:33,101 --> 00:47:36,301
"I can't do it, I can't climb,
I'm afraid!"

840
00:47:36,302 --> 00:47:39,602
Were you ever up that high
with only six inches of steel...

841
00:47:39,603 --> 00:47:41,703
...as a foothold between you and hell?

842
00:47:41,704 --> 00:47:44,204
What have you got to live for
if you're so afraid of dying?

843
00:47:46,105 --> 00:47:49,005
By the way, have you got
any life insurance?

844
00:47:51,506 --> 00:47:54,006
Oh, what a guy.

845
00:47:58,007 --> 00:48:00,407
Keep on using that same tonic.

846
00:48:00,408 --> 00:48:02,108
It's all the medicine you need.

847
00:48:02,109 --> 00:48:03,209
Yes, doctor.

848
00:48:03,210 --> 00:48:05,810
I don't think it'll be necessary
for me to come back again.

849
00:48:05,811 --> 00:48:07,811
How long is he gonna be
laid up, Doctor?

850
00:48:07,812 --> 00:48:09,512
Well, that's up to him.

851
00:48:09,513 --> 00:48:11,483
You know, Mr. Allen,

852
00:48:11,484 --> 00:48:15,284
I think your trouble's much more
mental than physical.

853
00:48:15,285 --> 00:48:17,785
It's my nerves, Doctor.

854
00:48:17,786 --> 00:48:21,800
They're troublesome things. Knock you out
when they get the best of you.

855
00:48:21,801 --> 00:48:24,000
- Yeah.
- But you got to knock them out.

856
00:48:24,001 --> 00:48:26,101
It can be done, you know.

857
00:48:26,102 --> 00:48:28,102
Get a grip on yourself.

858
00:48:28,103 --> 00:48:29,999
- Oh, Doctor.
- Hm?

859
00:48:30,000 --> 00:48:32,000
- About your bill.
- Oh, yes.

860
00:48:32,001 --> 00:48:36,101
My visit and the medicine, $9.

861
00:48:36,102 --> 00:48:38,332
Well, what I wanted to say was...

862
00:48:38,333 --> 00:48:41,100
You wouldn't mind waiting
for it, Doctor?

863
00:48:41,101 --> 00:48:44,601
I haven't got the nine dollars
just now.

864
00:48:44,602 --> 00:48:46,102
Is it that bad, son?

865
00:48:46,103 --> 00:48:48,603
- But you said I'll get well soon.
- Yes.

866
00:48:48,604 --> 00:48:52,000
When I get back to working
I'll pay you back with interest.

867
00:48:52,001 --> 00:48:54,400
That's all right, don't worry.

868
00:48:54,401 --> 00:48:55,901
Just get well.

869
00:48:56,602 --> 00:48:58,102
Goodbye.

870
00:49:01,203 --> 00:49:02,733
Oh, Mrs. Allen.

871
00:49:04,534 --> 00:49:07,134
If there's no money, how about food?

872
00:49:07,135 --> 00:49:10,385
Our credit's still good.
I'll see he gets it somehow.

873
00:49:10,386 --> 00:49:12,886
That'll be fine.
But get him out in the open.

874
00:49:12,887 --> 00:49:15,567
- This place is so stuffy.
- It's that maid!

875
00:49:15,568 --> 00:49:17,900
- I'll see about it right away, Doctor.
- Good, good.

876
00:49:17,901 --> 00:49:19,601
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye, Doctor.

877
00:49:20,002 --> 00:49:22,000
Lizzie! Hey, Lizzie!

878
00:49:22,001 --> 00:49:24,001
- Yessum?
- Come up here!

879
00:49:26,402 --> 00:49:27,902
Can you imagine me living
in a place...

880
00:49:27,903 --> 00:49:30,200
...that even a stranger has to make
cracks about us being dirty?

881
00:49:30,201 --> 00:49:31,751
- You want me, Mrs. Allen?
- I sure do!

882
00:49:31,752 --> 00:49:33,800
What's the idea of passing up this place
when you're cleaning the rooms?

883
00:49:33,801 --> 00:49:36,001
Oh, it's no use starting
anything, Shirley.

884
00:49:36,002 --> 00:49:37,802
Well, there's going to be trouble
anyway, Mrs. Allen.

885
00:49:37,803 --> 00:49:39,223
Mrs. Smith said to me this morning...

886
00:49:39,224 --> 00:49:42,450
...cause you ain't paid your rent for
so long she's gonna ask you to get out.

887
00:49:42,451 --> 00:49:43,751
But she can't do that.

888
00:49:43,752 --> 00:49:46,422
That's a nice one. Put a sick man
out in the street, eh?

889
00:49:46,423 --> 00:49:48,300
Says you owe her fifteen bucks.

890
00:49:48,301 --> 00:49:52,500
But I'll pay her, I'll pay it all back to
her as soon as I get back to work.

891
00:49:52,501 --> 00:49:54,301
That's what I told her, Mr. Allen.

892
00:49:54,302 --> 00:49:58,602
She says herself you was always on time
with your rent when you was living with...

893
00:49:59,703 --> 00:50:01,000
Before she came.

894
00:50:01,001 --> 00:50:03,401
Oh, so that's the story they're
telling downstairs, is it?

895
00:50:03,402 --> 00:50:05,500
Soon as he married me he got broke.

896
00:50:05,501 --> 00:50:07,600
No, no, she didn't say that, Shirley.

897
00:50:07,601 --> 00:50:09,701
Look here, you go tell Mrs. Smith
I want to see her.

898
00:50:09,702 --> 00:50:11,752
I'm gonna give that gossiper
a little surprise.

899
00:50:11,753 --> 00:50:15,443
Oh, I'll tell her, but I wouldn't advise
you to start nothing funny with her.

900
00:50:15,444 --> 00:50:18,744
- Her brother's a cop, you know.
- You go tell her what I said.

901
00:50:19,745 --> 00:50:22,100
Oh, it's no use starting
anything, Shirley.

902
00:50:23,001 --> 00:50:25,881
You'd better start packing
what little's left of our things.

903
00:50:25,882 --> 00:50:27,500
Oh, no, we ain't leaving here.

904
00:50:27,501 --> 00:50:29,500
But she won't trust us
for any more.

905
00:50:29,501 --> 00:50:32,000
I ain't asking her to. I'm gonna
pay what's owed her.

906
00:50:32,001 --> 00:50:33,701
What with?

907
00:50:38,402 --> 00:50:40,880
- Where'd you get that?
- Oh, don't get excited.

908
00:50:40,881 --> 00:50:42,051
- Where'd you get it?
- Borrowed it.

909
00:50:42,052 --> 00:50:43,800
- Who from?
- Tony.

910
00:50:43,801 --> 00:50:44,901
Tony?

911
00:50:44,902 --> 00:50:46,462
It's an advance, I'm going back
to work for him.

912
00:50:46,463 --> 00:50:48,143
But I told you I didn't want you to.

913
00:50:48,144 --> 00:50:50,624
I ain't going back to dancing.
He's putting on a floor show.

914
00:50:50,625 --> 00:50:52,325
I'm going to do a specialty,
a sing and dancing act.

915
00:50:52,326 --> 00:50:54,426
- You're lying.
- I am not!

916
00:50:54,427 --> 00:50:56,927
That's a nice note. You ain't got
a dime to your name.

917
00:50:56,928 --> 00:50:58,728
Then when I use my brains
and my talent to get some...

918
00:50:58,729 --> 00:51:00,350
...you start thinking dirty things
about me.

919
00:51:00,351 --> 00:51:02,400
I know why Tony gave you
that money.

920
00:51:02,401 --> 00:51:05,000
Bud warned me.

921
00:51:05,001 --> 00:51:07,701
- But I wouldn't listen to him.
- Bud, always Bud!

922
00:51:07,702 --> 00:51:09,980
That guy's still messing into with my life
even after he's dead.

923
00:51:09,981 --> 00:51:11,981
You give that money back,
give it back, do you hear?

924
00:51:11,982 --> 00:51:15,082
- I won't let you keep it, I tell you.
- I ain't asking you if I can, I'm doing it.

925
00:51:15,083 --> 00:51:18,333
I could have walked out any time these past
months and left you flat, couldn't I?

926
00:51:18,334 --> 00:51:20,234
I could be living like a queen
if I had wanted to.

927
00:51:20,235 --> 00:51:23,235
But I didn't do it, did I?
I've had offers, yes, plenty of them.

928
00:51:23,236 --> 00:51:25,136
Even since I teamed up with you.

929
00:51:25,137 --> 00:51:26,600
But I turned them all down.

930
00:51:26,601 --> 00:51:29,601
And what for? To struggle
along with you.

931
00:51:29,602 --> 00:51:31,300
Well, I'm through struggling, see?

932
00:51:31,301 --> 00:51:34,401
I'm at the end of my rope and I don't
want to hang so I'm hauling in.

933
00:51:34,402 --> 00:51:35,902
Get the idea?

934
00:51:35,903 --> 00:51:38,103
Alright, then take that money
and clear out of here.

935
00:51:38,104 --> 00:51:40,804
Oh, no, whether you want me
or not, I stick.

936
00:51:40,805 --> 00:51:42,705
There's no use you putting
on an act, John.

937
00:51:42,706 --> 00:51:44,506
You didn't know where the money
came from, you took it...

938
00:51:44,507 --> 00:51:46,907
...and ate what it bought and it
didn't poison you, I notice.

939
00:51:46,908 --> 00:51:48,888
Now that you know, what difference
does it make?

940
00:51:48,889 --> 00:51:51,100
I didn't know what kind of
money it was.

941
00:51:51,801 --> 00:51:54,461
Oh, I don't know what keeps
me from killing you.

942
00:51:54,462 --> 00:51:56,862
If you did, the goose would stop
laying the golden eggs.

943
00:51:56,863 --> 00:51:59,463
- I hate you!
- I don't doubt it.

944
00:51:59,464 --> 00:52:03,000
But I'm gonna do that song and dance
at Tony's like I said I was.

945
00:52:03,001 --> 00:52:07,701
And get this. No matter what you do, whether
you're taking the money or not, I am.

946
00:52:11,402 --> 00:52:12,702
Come in.

947
00:52:13,803 --> 00:52:15,803
You want to see me, Mrs. Allen?

948
00:52:15,804 --> 00:52:19,000
It's Mr. Allen, he's got
something for you.

949
00:52:20,101 --> 00:52:22,001
Yes, Mr. Allen?

950
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:25,999
Here.

951
00:52:26,700 --> 00:52:29,100
Here's the rent I owe you.

952
00:52:35,101 --> 00:52:37,501
Fifteen dollars is all you owe.

953
00:52:37,652 --> 00:52:39,102
Thanks.

954
00:53:10,003 --> 00:53:12,703
Well, big boy, what do I
look like now?

955
00:53:13,304 --> 00:53:15,004
You look just like what you are.

956
00:53:15,005 --> 00:53:18,705
Yeah, I look like the wife of
John Allen the good provider.

957
00:53:20,606 --> 00:53:22,006
Get those things out of here.

958
00:53:22,707 --> 00:53:25,207
- Take those clothes off.
- Oh, no, I just put them on.

959
00:53:25,208 --> 00:53:29,308
A few jealous cats are gonna see what
it means to make a successful marriage.

960
00:53:29,309 --> 00:53:32,409
Now see here!
I ain't standing for this any longer.

961
00:53:32,410 --> 00:53:34,910
I stood for you paying the rent
because I couldn't help myself.

962
00:53:34,911 --> 00:53:37,211
But if you go out with them things on,

963
00:53:37,212 --> 00:53:39,612
advertise what you brought me to,
you can stay out.

964
00:53:39,613 --> 00:53:43,473
You got it backwards, big boy.
I'm feeding the kitty now, see?

965
00:53:43,474 --> 00:53:46,000
There ain't anybody gonna bring
that kind of money into this house.

966
00:53:46,001 --> 00:53:47,001
That kind of money.

967
00:53:47,002 --> 00:53:50,402
Since when did you begin to examine
a dollar and see who it's father was?

968
00:53:50,803 --> 00:53:55,603
What do you want to stay here for
when you're doing so well by yourself?

969
00:53:55,604 --> 00:53:59,704
I found out that a missus can get away
with things that a miss can't.

970
00:53:59,705 --> 00:54:02,999
That's why all the girls all look up to me
and try to get tips on how I do it.

971
00:54:03,000 --> 00:54:06,600
Yeah, you give them the tips alright.

972
00:54:06,601 --> 00:54:09,501
You'll have them as low as you are
before you're through.

973
00:54:09,802 --> 00:54:11,702
Why shouldn't I give them a hand?

974
00:54:11,703 --> 00:54:13,603
That is, the ones that are worth it.

975
00:54:13,604 --> 00:54:15,700
I've only found one so far.

976
00:54:15,999 --> 00:54:18,901
You'd be interested in her.
You introduced her to me.

977
00:54:18,902 --> 00:54:21,202
- I never introduced you to any girl.
- Sure you did!

978
00:54:21,203 --> 00:54:23,103
At Bud's funeral.

979
00:54:24,204 --> 00:54:26,304
- Annie?
- That's the one.

980
00:54:26,305 --> 00:54:27,400
She's been around a couple of times...

981
00:54:27,401 --> 00:54:29,600
...to see if I couldn't get Tony
to take her on at the hall.

982
00:54:29,601 --> 00:54:31,151
You mean...

983
00:54:31,302 --> 00:54:34,402
- You mean you're gonna put Annie on...
- Why shouldn't I give her a break?

984
00:54:34,403 --> 00:54:36,003
- You can't do that.
- Do what?

985
00:54:36,004 --> 00:54:40,104
You can't... you can't make
a tramp out of Annie!

986
00:54:40,105 --> 00:54:43,200
Who's making anything out of her?
She's tired of working at the box factory.

987
00:54:43,201 --> 00:54:44,301
None of the fellows ever take her out...

988
00:54:44,302 --> 00:54:45,802
...and she wants me to put her
next to some good times.

989
00:54:45,803 --> 00:54:48,903
You can't do that! She was Buddy's steady
company. He was going to marry her.

990
00:54:49,404 --> 00:54:51,404
I don't care what you do
to yourself or to me.

991
00:54:51,405 --> 00:54:53,205
But you can't do anything
like that to her.

992
00:54:53,206 --> 00:54:55,456
- Say, do you think I...
- Leave her alone, do you hear?

993
00:54:55,457 --> 00:54:58,257
- Don't make me laugh, it'll crack my lips.
- Now listen to me, Shirley.

994
00:54:58,258 --> 00:55:00,800
You can do what you want to your own life
but don't go messing into Bud's.

995
00:55:00,801 --> 00:55:03,201
Who's messing into it?
Did I go after his girl?

996
00:55:03,202 --> 00:55:05,602
No! She comes up and makes
a proposition herself.

997
00:55:05,603 --> 00:55:07,703
And anyway, is she any better
than I am?

998
00:55:07,704 --> 00:55:10,904
If it's all right for me to work this way,
why is she too good for it?

999
00:55:14,005 --> 00:55:16,605
Here's a buck in case you run
out of cigarettes or something.

1000
00:55:36,706 --> 00:55:38,606
Hiya, John!

1001
00:55:40,407 --> 00:55:42,207
- What do you want?
- Ain't you seen the papers?

1002
00:55:42,208 --> 00:55:44,708
- What about the papers?
- The horses.

1003
00:55:44,709 --> 00:55:47,500
The horses? You mean the ones I...

1004
00:55:47,501 --> 00:55:49,800
You sure picked them pretty
this time, John.

1005
00:55:49,801 --> 00:55:51,201
You mean the horses won?

1006
00:55:51,202 --> 00:55:53,700
The whole layout. Niftiest parlay
I've ever seen.

1007
00:55:53,701 --> 00:55:55,901
- In the second Jean King comes up...
- How much?

1008
00:55:56,302 --> 00:55:58,402
- How much did I make?
- $388!

1009
00:55:58,403 --> 00:56:01,303
- 388?
- Not bad for a vice, huh?

1010
00:56:01,304 --> 00:56:03,564
I'll bet that partner of yours sure
would like to have been in on this.

1011
00:56:03,565 --> 00:56:06,565
I didn't have no partner!
I was in this alone.

1012
00:56:06,566 --> 00:56:08,466
I mean the fellow you used
to bunk with.

1013
00:56:08,467 --> 00:56:10,577
- Bud?
- Yeah, that's him.

1014
00:56:10,578 --> 00:56:12,600
Remember how he always
used to play for a big kill?

1015
00:56:12,601 --> 00:56:15,900
All the boys are talking about this.
They want to know where you got your tip.

1016
00:56:15,901 --> 00:56:17,400
No, no. it was not tip.

1017
00:56:17,999 --> 00:56:20,401
Yeah... yes, it was.

1018
00:56:21,202 --> 00:56:23,800
I got it from Bud, that's who.

1019
00:56:23,853 --> 00:56:26,103
- Which Bud?
- Yeah, he made me lay that bet.

1020
00:56:26,104 --> 00:56:27,800
He showed me how to play
them horses.

1021
00:56:27,801 --> 00:56:30,031
Hey, what are you talking about?
He's been under the ground for months.

1022
00:56:30,032 --> 00:56:32,832
- Where's the money, where is it?
- Don't get excited, you'll get it.

1023
00:56:32,833 --> 00:56:34,133
Three hundred and eighty-eight.

1024
00:56:34,134 --> 00:56:37,034
You'll be able to clear up
a lot of debts with $388.

1025
00:56:37,035 --> 00:56:38,600
Yeah, you bet I will.

1026
00:56:38,601 --> 00:56:40,701
I'll clear them all off.

1027
00:56:40,702 --> 00:56:43,402
Yeah, that's what Bud would
have wanted me to do.

1028
00:56:43,403 --> 00:56:45,673
That's why he showed me how
to play them horses.

1029
00:56:45,674 --> 00:56:48,800
- Say, I wouldn't talk like that.
- Yes, I've got it all written down here.

1030
00:56:48,801 --> 00:56:51,101
Nine dollars for the doctor.

1031
00:56:51,102 --> 00:56:53,202
Fifteen for the back room rent.

1032
00:56:53,203 --> 00:56:54,603
And then seven and a half.

1033
00:56:54,604 --> 00:56:56,504
I've got it all written down here.

1034
00:56:56,505 --> 00:56:58,505
Here, give me a pencil,
give me a pencil quick.

1035
00:56:58,506 --> 00:57:00,406
I can remember every cent of it.

1036
00:57:00,407 --> 00:57:03,407
There... nine dollars...

1037
00:57:03,408 --> 00:57:06,208
Fifteen... seven and a half...

1038
00:57:07,109 --> 00:57:08,309
There.

1039
00:57:09,610 --> 00:57:11,710
And this dollar!

1040
00:57:13,011 --> 00:57:13,811
Yeah...

1041
00:57:15,412 --> 00:57:18,012
That's a hundred and sixty-two.

1042
00:57:18,013 --> 00:57:20,400
A hundred and sixty-two dollars.

1043
00:57:21,201 --> 00:57:23,501
Not counting what he gave her.

1044
00:57:23,502 --> 00:57:26,666
But this is the only part of it
I've got to clear off!

1045
00:57:26,667 --> 00:57:27,967
What are you saying?

1046
00:57:27,968 --> 00:57:31,000
- Here, give me the money, give me $162.
- There's three hundred and eighty-eight.

1047
00:57:31,001 --> 00:57:33,131
No, I don't want it!
I only want 162!

1048
00:57:34,832 --> 00:57:38,300
No... No, I...

1049
00:57:38,301 --> 00:57:40,401
I gotta have another ten.

1050
00:57:40,402 --> 00:57:42,802
Yeah, I gotta have another ten-spot.

1051
00:57:42,803 --> 00:57:45,703
Yeah, that's for... never mind.

1052
00:57:45,704 --> 00:57:47,404
Give me 172.

1053
00:57:47,405 --> 00:57:50,605
- Take it all.
- I don't want it, I want 172!

1054
00:57:52,006 --> 00:57:53,906
That's mine, isn't it?

1055
00:57:54,607 --> 00:57:57,907
I didn't get this from him
or from her, did I?

1056
00:57:57,908 --> 00:57:59,608
Take it easy, take it easy!

1057
00:57:59,809 --> 00:58:01,409
Yeah, yeah...

1058
00:58:01,410 --> 00:58:03,110
Yeah, I gotta take it easy.

1059
00:58:03,711 --> 00:58:07,111
Yeah, I got a lot of things to do.

1060
00:58:07,112 --> 00:58:09,712
Give me a cigarette, will you?

1061
00:58:09,713 --> 00:58:11,513
Yeah, that'll steady me a bit.

1062
00:58:11,514 --> 00:58:13,314
Light it for me, will you?

1063
00:58:13,315 --> 00:58:16,215
Eighty, ninety, a hundred and ten...

1064
00:58:16,216 --> 00:58:19,116
A hundred and fifty,
a hundred and fifty-two...

1065
00:58:19,717 --> 00:58:22,217
A hundred and sixty.

1066
00:58:22,218 --> 00:58:23,999
Sixty-one, two...

1067
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:26,200
There, take that back.

1068
00:58:26,601 --> 00:58:28,001
Thanks.

1069
00:58:28,702 --> 00:58:32,002
Yeah... yeah, I got something to do.

1070
00:58:33,103 --> 00:58:36,103
Yeah, just a minute, just a minute.

1071
00:58:48,204 --> 00:58:50,444
- You see this?
- It's a teacup.

1072
00:58:50,445 --> 00:58:52,200
Yeah, that's what you think it is.

1073
00:58:52,201 --> 00:58:54,701
But it ain't, it's more than that.

1074
00:58:54,702 --> 00:58:57,102
I've carried it with me
wherever I've gone.

1075
00:58:57,103 --> 00:58:59,603
I've had to hide it so she
wouldn't find it.

1076
00:59:00,404 --> 00:59:03,804
Once this was filled with
bootleg liquor.

1077
00:59:03,999 --> 00:59:06,105
That's what started it all.

1078
00:59:06,106 --> 00:59:09,200
And then it was filled with the blood
of my dearest friend.

1079
00:59:09,201 --> 00:59:11,200
My buddy, you understand?

1080
00:59:11,201 --> 00:59:14,201
And now it's filled with
rotten money, see?

1081
00:59:14,902 --> 00:59:18,100
But I'm gonna clean it all out now, see?
That's what I need the money for.

1082
00:59:18,101 --> 00:59:20,701
I'm gonna pay it all back,
I gonna be free!

1083
00:59:21,602 --> 00:59:23,002
Yeah!

1084
00:59:23,003 --> 00:59:24,703
I'm gonna be free!

1085
00:59:39,504 --> 00:59:42,404
- How much are they?
- Only sixty-five bucks.

1086
00:59:43,405 --> 00:59:45,805
Well, I ain't asking you for
real ones, Tony.

1087
00:59:45,806 --> 00:59:48,206
I suppose I'll have to buy
them for you.

1088
00:59:48,207 --> 00:59:50,107
Give me the money.
I got them all picked out.

1089
00:59:50,108 --> 00:59:51,808
Oh, you have, eh?

1090
00:59:52,709 --> 00:59:55,509
You knew I'd give in, didn't you?

1091
01:00:00,510 --> 01:00:01,980
- John!
- What are you doing here?

1092
01:00:01,981 --> 01:00:04,100
- What did you come here for anyway?
- You!

1093
01:00:04,122 --> 01:00:05,900
What are you trying to do,
spoil everything?

1094
01:00:05,901 --> 01:00:07,801
Oh, no, I'm going to set
everything straight.

1095
01:00:07,802 --> 01:00:10,000
What is this, a frame-up?
Are you two trying to frame me?

1096
01:00:10,001 --> 01:00:11,701
Oh, no, Tony, I ain't in on this,
I swear it!

1097
01:00:11,702 --> 01:00:14,302
Trying to pull the outraged husband
gag on me, are you?

1098
01:00:14,303 --> 01:00:16,000
- Well, we'll see about that.
- You stay where you are!

1099
01:00:16,001 --> 01:00:17,401
- What is this?
- Look!

1100
01:00:17,402 --> 01:00:19,102
I've got it all written down here.

1101
01:00:19,103 --> 01:00:20,983
Nine dollars for the doctor,
fifteen for the room rent...

1102
01:00:20,984 --> 01:00:23,300
- What is this anyway?
- Forty-five dollars more for the rent.

1103
01:00:23,301 --> 01:00:25,601
And here's for the food.
I've got it all written down here.

1104
01:00:25,602 --> 01:00:28,602
- It all adds up to $162.
- I don't know what you're talking about.

1105
01:00:28,603 --> 01:00:30,000
What do you think you're doing
anyway, John?

1106
01:00:30,001 --> 01:00:31,900
I'm trying to square things
with myself, that's what.

1107
01:00:31,901 --> 01:00:34,500
$162, that's what I took off of him.

1108
01:00:34,501 --> 01:00:37,801
Well, I've got the $162 now,
I'm giving them back.

1109
01:00:37,802 --> 01:00:40,102
Here it is, a hundred and sixty-two.

1110
01:00:40,103 --> 01:00:41,980
You can count it if you want to,
it's all there.

1111
01:00:41,981 --> 01:00:44,181
- I don't want your money!
- You can't get out of it that way!

1112
01:00:44,182 --> 01:00:45,782
It's yours, take it, see?

1113
01:00:45,783 --> 01:00:48,283
- And now, you!
- Tony!

1114
01:00:48,284 --> 01:00:50,900
Yeah, it was you who made
a rat out of me.

1115
01:00:50,901 --> 01:00:54,101
Made me ashamed so I couldn't
hold my face up.

1116
01:00:54,102 --> 01:00:56,502
But I paid him off now.

1117
01:00:56,503 --> 01:00:58,700
And as soon as I've paid you I'm gonna
be square with everyone.

1118
01:00:58,701 --> 01:01:00,801
- Tony!
- No, I ain't gonna hurt you, Tony.

1119
01:01:00,802 --> 01:01:02,902
It was a business deal
with you, see?

1120
01:01:02,903 --> 01:01:04,803
- But her!
- Give me another chance, John,

1121
01:01:04,804 --> 01:01:08,504
- I'll play fair, I swear I will.
- Oh, no, you can't, Shirley.

1122
01:01:08,505 --> 01:01:11,705
Buddy was right.
You were born rotten.

1123
01:01:11,706 --> 01:01:15,000
And now you're trying to make
other girls as rotten as you are.

1124
01:01:15,001 --> 01:01:17,171
No, I ain't... I won't touch that Annie
girl if you don't want me to.

1125
01:01:17,172 --> 01:01:18,972
No, no, it ain't her especially.

1126
01:01:18,973 --> 01:01:21,073
She only helped put me
wise to you.

1127
01:01:21,074 --> 01:01:25,374
You told me to think about where the money
comes from that I've been spending.

1128
01:01:25,375 --> 01:01:27,600
Well, I have thought about it.

1129
01:01:27,601 --> 01:01:30,201
- And that's why I'm here.
- Tony, he's going to kill me!

1130
01:01:30,202 --> 01:01:33,342
- Yeah, I'm gonna kill you.
- No! No!

1131
01:01:33,343 --> 01:01:35,443
If I don't, you're gonna
go on like this.

1132
01:01:35,444 --> 01:01:37,644
From Tony to another man
and from him to somebody else.

1133
01:01:37,645 --> 01:01:39,845
Always making yourself cheaper
and dirtier.

1134
01:01:39,846 --> 01:01:42,456
No I won't, no I won't! If you let me alone,
I swear I'll be on the level.

1135
01:01:42,457 --> 01:01:44,157
Yeah, that's what you think now,
but you won't.

1136
01:01:44,158 --> 01:01:47,158
It will be the best thing for all
of us if I stop it right now.

1137
01:01:48,359 --> 01:01:51,159
Help! Help!

1138
01:01:54,860 --> 01:01:59,260
And so, young man, my personal
desire is to be lenient with you...

1139
01:01:59,261 --> 01:02:02,261
...in view of certain extenuating
circumstances in the case.

1140
01:02:02,262 --> 01:02:06,262
Unfortunately, however, I am bound
by the dictates of the law.

1141
01:02:06,999 --> 01:02:09,900
Just why you didn't permit your council
to make any defense for you...

1142
01:02:09,901 --> 01:02:11,301
I don't know.

1143
01:02:11,302 --> 01:02:14,502
It seems to me you could very well
have pleaded justification.

1144
01:02:14,503 --> 01:02:17,000
Or you might have pleaded
temporary insanity.

1145
01:02:17,001 --> 01:02:20,301
The evidence of the detectives
who arrested you at the steelworks...

1146
01:02:20,302 --> 01:02:22,802
...indicates a least a temporary
mental derangement.

1147
01:02:23,303 --> 01:02:27,203
However, since you refused to take
advantage of any of these defenses,

1148
01:02:27,404 --> 01:02:32,304
there is no alternative left me than to find
you guilty of murder in the first degree...

1149
01:02:32,305 --> 01:02:34,905
...and sentence you to death
in the electric chair.

1150
01:02:36,006 --> 01:02:38,406
Is there anything you wish to say...

1151
01:02:38,407 --> 01:02:40,907
...before I pass formal sentence
upon you?

1152
01:02:46,308 --> 01:02:52,900
All that you said about the
shooting being premeditated,

1153
01:02:53,501 --> 01:02:55,901
is quite true, Your Honor.

1154
01:02:55,902 --> 01:02:58,702
Yeah, I did it just like you heard.

1155
01:02:59,503 --> 01:03:02,803
I was never quite sure when
I'd be able to do it.

1156
01:03:02,804 --> 01:03:05,804
But something inside of me
kept hoping that...

1157
01:03:05,805 --> 01:03:09,005
...someday, somehow I'd be able to.

1158
01:03:10,306 --> 01:03:13,999
Maybe that's why I played the ponies.

1159
01:03:14,000 --> 01:03:16,900
Played them without really knowing why.

1160
01:03:16,901 --> 01:03:19,701
As soon as that bookie told me
how much I'd won,

1161
01:03:19,702 --> 01:03:22,442
I knew at once what I had to do.

1162
01:03:22,443 --> 01:03:25,500
No, I wasn't crazy, Your Honor.

1163
01:03:25,501 --> 01:03:27,801
I knew all along what I was doing.

1164
01:03:27,999 --> 01:03:29,702
Yeah, I was...

1165
01:03:29,703 --> 01:03:33,303
What I can't understand now...

1166
01:03:33,304 --> 01:03:36,404
is why you're giving me
the chair for that.

1167
01:03:36,905 --> 01:03:40,105
You... you've got it all wrong, see?

1168
01:03:41,206 --> 01:03:46,006
If you'd have burned me
when I was living off of her,

1169
01:03:46,607 --> 01:03:50,107
that would have been the right
time to do it, see?

1170
01:03:51,508 --> 01:03:55,808
At first I thought I'd only take what
I needed, what I had to have.

1171
01:03:55,809 --> 01:03:59,409
It wasn't my fault I had to have it
and I couldn't get it myself.

1172
01:04:01,510 --> 01:04:04,910
But I knew where it was coming from.

1173
01:04:04,911 --> 01:04:07,211
And I took it just the same.

1174
01:04:07,212 --> 01:04:11,000
That's when you should have
given me the chair!

1175
01:04:11,001 --> 01:04:14,501
I sunk as low as a guy can get.

1176
01:04:14,502 --> 01:04:17,302
Yeah, but nobody did anything to me.

1177
01:04:19,003 --> 01:04:25,103
And then I got that break with
the ponies like I was telling you.

1178
01:04:25,104 --> 01:04:27,404
And when I got it,
what did I do with it?

1179
01:04:27,405 --> 01:04:30,005
Blow it in on a good time? No!

1180
01:04:30,806 --> 01:04:35,206
I went out and I paid off my
debt to him...

1181
01:04:35,207 --> 01:04:36,607
...and to her.

1182
01:04:36,608 --> 01:04:41,008
Yeah, I did it so I could hold
my face up again.

1183
01:04:41,999 --> 01:04:45,209
And for that you want to kill me.

1184
01:04:46,710 --> 01:04:52,410
Well, don't you see? You're killing
me at the wrong time.

1185
01:04:52,411 --> 01:04:56,811
If you'd have killed me
when I was a rat,

1186
01:04:56,812 --> 01:04:59,100
I'd have thanked you for it,
but you didn't.

1187
01:04:59,101 --> 01:05:02,401
And now that I've squared everything
off you want to kill me.

1188
01:05:02,402 --> 01:05:04,802
Well it ain't fair!

1189
01:05:06,003 --> 01:05:12,203
It ain't fair to let a rat live
and kill a man.

1190
01:05:12,204 --> 01:05:14,804
No, it ain't reasonable!

1191
01:05:14,805 --> 01:05:17,005
It don't make sense.

1192
01:05:18,506 --> 01:05:21,306
I won't let you do it, I tell you!

1193
01:05:21,307 --> 01:05:23,607
I won't!

1194
01:05:25,008 --> 01:05:30,708
You're only gonna make me sick
like I was when Buddy fell.

1195
01:05:31,809 --> 01:05:35,209
You're gonna bring that fever
back on me again.

1196
01:05:35,210 --> 01:05:40,010
No, I don't want to get sick.
I can't!

1197
01:05:40,011 --> 01:05:43,811
I got a lot of things to explain
to you yet.

1198
01:05:44,912 --> 01:05:48,912
You're bringing that fever
back on me again.

1199
01:05:50,613 --> 01:05:53,213
The blood's rushing to my head.

1200
01:05:53,214 --> 01:05:58,999
Oh, I'm getting all dizzy...
My thoughts are all getting jammed up.

1201
01:05:59,000 --> 01:06:03,000
Stop it, you!
Stop it!

1202
01:06:03,001 --> 01:06:09,300
Stop it! What are you doing?
Stop it, stop it!

1203
01:06:11,401 --> 01:06:14,700
Buddy... don't go away!

1204
01:06:14,999 --> 01:06:17,201
Wait for me.

1205
01:06:17,202 --> 01:06:19,402
I'm coming.

1206
01:06:19,403 --> 01:06:22,903
Bud! Wait for me!

1207
01:06:31,204 --> 01:06:32,804
All right, Doctor.

1208
